[1] Serotype O, porcine
Date: Wed 10 Jan 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(02) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25614


Foot-and-mouth disease, China (People's Rep of)
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on 10 Jan 2018 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Jan 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 8 Jan 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 7 Apr 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of the outbreaks, total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Buyi and Miao Autonomous Prefecture of QianNan, Sandu, Guizhou
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Jan 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 40 / 0 / 0 / 40 / 0
Swine / 1520 / 42 / 25 / 1453 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0 / 0 / - / 100
Swine / 2.76 / 1.64 / 59.52 / 97.24
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; screening; quarantine; official destruction of animals products; stamping out; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Lanzhou National Reference Laboratory Foot and Mouth Disease (OIE reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swine / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 8 Jan 2018 / Positive
Swine / virus isolation / 8 Jan 2018 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

